7|0|6|http://ibnkhaldun.cs.purdue.edu:8181/limo/gwtmaps/|2340FA9687BBBA633B8360439C75EB4C|example.edu.client.service.ExampleService|runScript|java.lang.String/2004016611|# Program 6: while loop and conditional if
# Similar to Program 5 but instead of writing sequential programs while loop is utilized 
# This program performs visualization task, identifies number of points of interests,
# add marker, add message on each location then compute the distance between
# pairs of points in a selected route
home = read_address("Ellen Dr", "Indianapolis", "IN", "46224")

POI_list = [["museum", ["3000 N Meridian St,", "Indianapolis", "IN",  "46208"]], 
            ["zoo", ["1200 W Washington St", "Indianapolis", "IN",  "46222"]], 
            ["speedway",["4790 W 16th St", "Indianapolis", "IN",  "46222"]], 
            ["park" , ["7840 W 56th St", "Indianapolis", "IN",  "46278"]]]

home_mk = display_marker(home)
display_message("Home", home_mk)
markers = []
i = 0
length =  len(POI_list)
while i < length:
  location = read_address(POI_list[i][1][0], POI_list[i][1][1], 
                          POI_list[i][1][2], POI_list[i][1][3])
  display_marker(location)
  markers.append(location)
  display_message(POI_list[i][0],location)
  if i == 0:
    print "Home" + " ---> " + POI_list [i][0]+ " " + \\
            str(round(compute_distance(markers[i], home_mk),1)) + "mi"
  else:
    print POI_list[i-1][0] + " ---> " + POI_list [i][0]+ " " + \\
            str(round(compute_distance(markers[i-1], markers[i]),1)) + "mi"
  i = i + 1

print POI_list [length-1][0] + " ---> " + "Home"+ " " + \\
            str(round(compute_distance(home_mk,markers[length-1]),1)) + "mi"|1|2|3|4|1|5|6|

# This program moves  the Commuter 1 mile showing the route taken by the Commuter.
address = read_address("1100 Hillcrest Rd", "West Lafayette", "IN", "47906")
display_message("Start", address)
my_location = get_location(address)
previous_location = my_location 
start_at("com1", address,"EAST")
distance= 1
direction =["SOUTH","WEST","NORTH","EAST"]
next_direction = 0

while( distance > 0.001):
  move_distance("com1", 0.01)
  current_location = get_current_point("com1")
  if(current_location == previous_location ):
    road  = get_road_names(current_location)
    turn_to("com1", road[0],direction[next_direction])
    next_direction += 1
    if(next_direction==4):
      next_direction=0
  distance = distance - compute_distance(previous_location , current_location)
  previous_location = current_location

show_on_map("com1")
Finish_location =  get_current_point("com1")
display_message("Finish",Finish_location)
print "Total distance traveled: " +str(display_distance("com1"))|1|2|3|4|1|5|6|

7|0|6|http://127.0.0.1:8888/gwtmaps/|2340FA9687BBBA633B8360439C75EB4C|example.edu.client.service.ExampleService|runScript|java.lang.String/2004016611|# Program 12: get (returns polygon), spatial operator: touches, and conditional if/else.
# This program displays the geometric shape and the center of Indiana, Ohio and
#  Iowa States, then tests if Indiana touches Iowa or Ohio.
Indiana_pol= get("Indiana", "STATE", "POLYGON")
display_shape(Indiana_pol)
Indiana_point= get("Indiana", "STATE", "POINT")
display_marker(Indiana_point)
Ohio_pol= get("Ohio", "STATE", "POLYGON")
display_shape(Ohio_pol)
Ohio_point= get("Ohio", "STATE", "POINT")
display_marker(Ohio_point)
Iowa_pol= get("Iowa", "STATE", "POLYGON")
display_shape(Iowa_pol)
Iowa_point= get("Iowa", "STATE", "POINT")
display_marker(Iowa_point)

if(touches(Indiana_pol, Ohio_pol)):
  print "Indiana touches Ohio"
if(touches(Indiana_pol, Iowa_pol)):
  print "Indiana touches Iowa"
if(disjoint(Indiana_pol, Ohio_pol)):
  print "Indiana and Ohio are disjoint"
if(disjoint(Indiana_pol, Iowa_pol)):
  print "Indiana and Iowa are disjoint"|1|2|3|4|1|5|6|
